      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of Ruth Morgensternová, which became a part of the Documentation campaign,
          Prague. She describes her fate from November 1942, when she was deported from the
          Theresienstadt ghetto until the liberation of the Bergen-Belsen camp in April 1945.
          Morgensternová is focusing on the living conditions in the Estonian labour camp Jägala, in
          which she was imprisoned. She also describes harsh situation of the inmates of the labour
          camp Ereda.</p>
      </abstract>
